bilingual.source: The door is next to the desk.
The desk is next to the door.
Did he knock on the door first?
Close the door and turn the key.

list.abstract: door，英语单词，名词，作名词时意为“门；家，户；门口；通道，人名；(英)多尔”。
Door是一个英文单词，词性为名词，发音英[dɔː(r)]、美[dɔːr] ，作名词时意为门、家，户、门口。

yingyinNormal.en: I have to get a lock for my door.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我一定要给我的门弄个锁。

yingyinNormal.en: Goodwin, open this god damn door！
yingyinNormal.zh: 戈德温，把这该死的门打开。

yingyinNormal.en: It opens a door I don't want to open.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这样会打开一扇我不想开的门。

yingyinNormal.en: Looks like the professor is about to test a door!
yingyinNormal.zh: 看来教授要测试门了。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, they're not locked in. The door just sticks.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他们没有被锁啊，门只是卡住了而已。

yingyinNormal.en: That's the door. Some chicken, love?
yingyinNormal.zh: 有人敲门。吃鸡肉吗，亲爱的？

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, I guess you can close the door now.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，我想你可以把门关上了。

yingyinNormal.en: Samantha, you go right through that door.
yingyinNormal.zh: 萨曼塔，就穿过那扇门。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, let me get the door first. Hi, no one!
yingyinNormal.zh: 我先去开门，没有人，你好。

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah, once he figures out how to work a door.
yingyinNormal.zh: 没错，等他学会如何开门以后。

yingyinNormal.en: Wax the door shut, we're never leaving, ever.
yingyinNormal.zh: 把门用腊封起来，我们再也不走了。

yingyinNormal.en: When this door closes, it will not open again.
yingyinNormal.zh: 当那扇门再次关上，就再也不会打开了。

yingyinNormal.en: How'd you escape? The old-fashioned way. Back door.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你怎么跑出来的？老办法，走后门。

yingyinNormal.en: You're joking, right? You guys just walked through the door.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你在说笑吧？你们才刚进门。

yingyinNormal.en: There's the door.
yingyinNormal.zh: 门在那儿。

yingyinNormal.en: It's because Door's open. What? It can't really be Room if Door's open.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是因为门开着。什么？门开着，这就不是房间了。

yingyinNormal.en: But it's not that bad. So what? It blocks a little of your door, a little of my door.
yingyinNormal.zh: 还好嘛，你的门挡一点点，我的门挡一点点。

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah, you know what? I got a better idea. How about it blocks none of my door, and a lot of your door?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我有更好的主意干脆不要挡我的门，都去挡你的门。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh it's going through the door. It's going up the stairs.
yingyinNormal.zh: 哦，它穿过了门！上了楼梯。

yingyinNormal.en: It turns out even though people in the better door were in the better door in a better relationship, they went back to the inferior door just to open it up to keep the options open.
yingyinNormal.zh: 实验证明，即使人们找到了更好的门，或者说他们找到了更适合相处的人，他们还是会去点击那些不理想的门让他们一直开着，不让这些选择消失。
